cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.AI, cs.DC, cs.SY

This paper is about intrusion detection in distributed systems, specifically in wireless sensor networks. The paper proposes an artificial immune model based on Danger theory and mobile agents to detect distributed denial-of-service attacks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also involves network protocols and message passing between agents, which suggests the sub-category cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The use of artificial immune systems and danger theory implies the sub-category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves modeling and simulation, which suggests the sub-category cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). Finally, the paper proposes a system that can detect malicious patterns with a high level of accuracy, which suggests the sub-category cs.SY (Systems and Control).
